Many programming groups have been torn apart and friendships ruined over code-formatting arguments.

Sometimes you have to accept an "ugly" solution if it's the only realistic strategy to fulfill your requirements.

Experienced C++ programmers never start a project from scratch.

As a good programming citizen, you should try to contribute to open-source projects if you find yourself reaping the benefits of open-source libraries.

Learning the C++ language and becoming a good C++ programmer are two very different things.
